headline: Jack Henry second-quarter profit rises on strong bank tech demand
summary: Jack Henry & Associates reported a higher second-quarter profit on Tuesday, driven by strong demand for its banking ​technology offerings. The Monett, Missouri-based company provides banks and credit ‌unions with technology and payment processing services for day-to-day operations such as taking deposits, ‌opening accounts and recording interest. Smaller financial institutions depend on banking technology providers such as Jack Henry, unlike Wall Street's biggest banks, which invest billions of dollars in developing proprietary tech stacks.

headline: Jack Henry: Fiscal Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The results surpassed Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $1.43 per share. The payment processsing company posted revenue of $619.3 million in the period, also exceeding Street forecasts.

headline: Jack Henry & Associates, Inc. Reports Second Quarter Fiscal 2026 Results
summary: Jack Henry & Associates, Inc. (Nasdaq: JKHY), a leading financial technology provider, today announced results for fiscal second quarter ended December 31, 2025.
